The Public Service Commission has on Friday shortlisted six candidates for the position of chairperson at the EACC.Retired Anglican Archbishop Eliud Wabukala is among those shortlisted for the position at the Ethics and Anti-corruption Commission.Others are William Kirwa, Philemon Mwaisaka, Peter Ondieki, Rose Osoro and Erastus Iguna.They are expected to appear for interviews on November 17 at PSC offices in Nairobi.The position of EACC chairman became vacant following the resignation of Philip Kinisu on August 31 after he was implicated in the Sh791 million NYS scandal.More on this: Kinisu's Esaki company cleared of wrongdoing over NYS scamA company associated with Kinisu is said to have received Sh35 million